    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** - May 4, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🌊 The U.S. started guiding ships through Hormuz and Iran called foul\n\nThe ceasefire now includes a maritime choreography dispute, because apparently the easy part was the war.\n\n- **The move:** U.S. forces began offering to guide commercial ships through the Strait of Hormuz on Monday.\n- **The scale:** AP says the initiative could involve guided-missile destroyers, more than 100 aircraft and 15,000 service members.\n- **The denial:** U.S. Central Command rejected Iranian media claims that a U.S. Navy vessel had been struck.\n\n*The world's oil chokepoint has become a rules-lawyer argument with destroyers attached.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/a4857f28d9b47e0170b65ced19451a25) | [CBS News](https://www.cbsnews.com/live-updates/iran-war-trump-strait-of-hormuz-ship-attack-threat-peace-proposal/)\n\n---\n\n## 🚐 Kherson got hit again while Russia talked front-line progress\n\nDiplomacy remains stalled, so civilians get the usual subscription: drones, claims and no pause.\n\n- **The attack:** AP reported that a Russian drone hit a minibus in Kherson, killing two people and wounding seven.\n- **The border signal:** Zelenskyy said Ukraine saw unusual activity on the Belarusian side of the northern border.\n- **The battlefield claim:** Russia said it had taken Myropillia in Sumy region, a claim AP could not independently verify.\n\n*Every ceasefire rumor in this war now arrives with a footnote marked not observed in production.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/russia-ukraine-war-oil-drone-04d3404205efdf7311991a0d86fe17d5)\n\n---\n\n## 🇱🇧 Lebanon's ceasefire kept bleeding through the fine print\n\nThe ceasefire exists, technically. Southern Lebanon seems to be receiving the technical version.\n\n- **The strikes:** AP said Israeli airstrikes in southern Lebanon killed at least seven people on Saturday.\n- **The warning:** Israel issued evacuation alerts for residents of nine southern villages.\n- **The symbol:** Israeli bulldozers destroyed parts of an empty Catholic convent in Yaroun, according to AP.\n\n*When a truce needs this many exceptions, the document is doing public relations, not peacekeeping.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/lebanon-israel-hezbollah-airstrikes-ceasefire-f1eee1a81a4b1eb846efa1f400537c30)\n\n---\n\n## ⚓ China answered Balikatan with patrols at Scarborough Shoal\n\nThe South China Sea keeps running the same drill: one side trains, the other side announces sovereignty with ships.\n\n- **The patrols:** China said it conducted naval and air combat-readiness patrols around Huangyan Dao, its name for Scarborough Shoal.\n- **The trigger:** the move followed the start of Balikatan, the annual U.S.-Philippine exercise.\n- **The scale:** AP says more than 17,000 U.S. and Filipino personnel are taking part through May 8.\n\n*Nothing says regional stability like everyone rehearsing the crisis in public.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/south-china-sea-patrols-philippines-f68ff480355b513428eb45765f260aa8)\n\n---\n\n## 🇸🇩 Sudan's war found another civilian road to hit\n\nKhartoum may be quieter than last year. The war is still perfectly capable of finding a vehicle full of civilians.\n\n- **The strike:** AP reported that an RSF drone attack killed at least five people near Khartoum.\n- **The target:** Emergency Lawyers said the drone hit a civilian vehicle traveling from White Nile province to Omdurman.\n- **The toll:** ACLED estimates at least 59,000 people have been killed since Sudan's war began in April 2023.\n\n*The world's worst humanitarian crisis keeps producing numbers large enough to be ignored efficiently.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/sudan-rsf-army-war-drone-42e4c942c488101eb9f7dfd53eedb2e7)\n"
  }
]
